Part 1

Generate data

n = 1000
data <- data.frame(x = 1:n,
                   y = 1 / (1 + exp(-seq(-5, 5, length.out = n))))

# add noise
data$y <- data$y + rnorm(n) * 0.05


ggplot(data) +
  geom_point(aes(x = x, y = y, color = "Data"), alpha = 1/2) +
  #ylim(0, 1) +
  labs(x = "t (time)", y = "y(t)", color = "",
       caption = "Source: the Lahman baseball database") + 
  theme_TS()

SETAR(2,1,1)

data$SETAR <- 0.4

ggplot(data) +
  geom_point(aes(x = x, y = y, color = "Data"), alpha = 1/2) +
  geom_line(aes(x = x, y = SETAR, color = "SETAR(2,1,1)"), alpha = 1/2) +
  #ylim(0, 1) +
  labs(x = "t (time)", y = "y(t)", color = "") +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(panel.background = element_blank(), 
        panel.border = element_blank(),
        panel.grid = element_blank())

IGAR(2;1)

MMAR(2;1).
